\section{Overview of DDCS Architecture}
The Distributed Digital Control System (DDCS) is a cutting-edge architecture
designed to manage the Instrumentation and Control (I\&C) of the PFBR. By
leveraging a robust, fault-tolerant three-tier design, the DDCS enhances
operational safety, reliability, and system efficiency.

\subsection{Three-Tier Structure}
\subsubsection{Bottom Tier: Control Nodes}
\begin{itemize}
 \item \textbf{Execution of Interlock Logic:} All interlock logics required
for reactor operation are processed within the control nodes.
 \item \textbf{Fail-Safe Mechanisms:} Routing fail-safe outputs to the plant
upon control node failure ensures operational continuity.
 \item \textbf{Input Management:} Synchronized exchange of inputs with other
nodes for coherent interlock execution.
 \item \textbf{Parameter Downloads:} Configurable parameters can be
downloaded to the control nodes on demand.
\end{itemize}

\subsubsection{Middle Tier: Process Computers}
\begin{itemize}
 \item \textbf{Data Processing:} Real-time data from control nodes is
processed for decision-making and monitoring.
 \item \textbf{Networking:} Secure communication bridge between control nodes
and display stations.
 \item \textbf{Command Execution:} Operator-initiated soft commands are
routed through process computers to the control nodes.
\end{itemize}

\subsubsection{Top Tier: Display Stations}
\begin{itemize}
 \item \textbf{Command Initiation:} Operators send soft commands directly to
control nodes.
 \item \textbf{Parameter Management:} Editing and monitoring of configurable
parameters.
 \item \textbf{Alarm Logic Visualization:} Alarm logic outputs provide
actionable insights to operators.
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Safety and Reliability Measures}
\begin{itemize}
 \item Fail-safe outputs ensure plant safety upon any system failure.
 \item Multiple redundancy layers across network and hardware minimize risk
of downtime.
 \item Compliance with SG-D-25 recommendations and nuclear safety regulatory
frameworks.
 \item Continuous monitoring and periodic testing sustain performance and
reliability.
\end{itemize}

